oc:kn_1ada8fb6 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building any formula in the model" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never allow circular references in the Excel model. Never hardcode projection numbers — all projections must flow from assumption inputs via formulas." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Circular references break Excel iteration and produce unreliable results. Hardcoded numbers defeat the dynamic nature of the model" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_220eb1c1 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always when formatting any financial model cell" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use industry-standard color coding: blue text for hardcoded inputs, black for formulas, green for cross-sheet links, red for errors/flags. No hardcoded numbers in projection formulas except constants." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Color coding makes the model auditable and instantly distinguishes assumptions from calculations" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_226167e4 a oc:Idempotency,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When modifying assumptions post-creation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The model is designed to be fully dynamic — changing any assumption should update all downstream calculations without requiring manual re-entry" ;
    oc:hasRationale "A dynamic model supports rapid scenario analysis and is the hallmark of professional financial modeling" .

oc:kn_826185c9 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Complete modeling workflow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Extract historical financials from 10-K (Income Statement, Cash Flow, Balance Sheet — 3-5 years) 2. Model Revenue (product 20-30 rows, geography 15-20 rows, channel) 3. Model Operating Expenses (COGS, R&D, S&M, G&A, D&A) 4. Build Income Statement (40-50 lines) 5. Build Cash Flow Statement 6. Build Balance Sheet with balance check 7. Build DCF Inputs tab 8. Build Scenarios (Bull/Base/Bear) 9. Run quality check" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_8b22367d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After completing all 6 tabs" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Run 10-point quality check: verify formulas, test assumption changes propagate, verify scenario switching, check color coding, confirm balance sheet balances, check for circular references, verify no hardcoded projection numbers, test cross-sheet links, verify revenue totals tie across tabs, review formatting." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Systematic validation catches errors that would undermine the model's credibility before it feeds into valuation and reporting" .

oc:kn_8d638190 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When modeling operating expenses (Step 3)" ;
    oc:directiveContent """OpEx modeling by department:
For each of R&D, S&M, G&A:
1. Model headcount × comp per head = personnel costs
2. Add other costs
3. Calculate total and % of revenue
4. Link D&A to CapEx schedule with depreciation rates""" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

oc:kn_9242f79c a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building and validating the Balance Sheet tab" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Balance sheet must balance for every year (Total Assets = Total Liabilities + Equity). Include a balance check row that flags OK/IMBALANCE." ;
    oc:hasRationale "An unbalanced balance sheet indicates formula errors and undermines credibility of the entire model" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_9ca15dc1 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When modeling revenue in Step 2" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Revenue model is the most critical part — invest 20-30 rows for product breakdown and 15-20 rows for geography breakdown with sub-categories, not just top-level totals. Revenue by product total must equal revenue by geography total." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Revenue drives all downstream projections; granular breakdowns reveal mix shifts and growth drivers that aggregate numbers hide" .

oc:kn_b4daaa0a a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building the Revenue Model tab" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "excel" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Revenue by Product/Category layout:
                        2021A   2022A   2023A   2024A   2025E   2026E   2027E   2028E   2029E
Product Category A
  Sub-product A1        XX      XX      XX      XX      XX      XX      XX      XX      XX
  ...
Category A Total       XX      XX      XX      XX      XX      XX      XX      XX      XX
  % of Total Rev       X%      X%      X%      X%      X%      X%      X%      X%      X%
  YoY Growth %          -       X%      X%      X%      X%      X%      X%      X%      X%
TOTAL REVENUE          XX      XX      XX      XX      XX      XX      XX      XX      XX""" .

oc:kn_bf038979 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building the Scenarios tab (Step 8)" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Scenario construction:
1. Define 3 assumption sets (Bull/Base/Bear) for: Revenue CAGR, Gross Margin 2029E, EBITDA Margin 2029E, CapEx % of Revenue
2. Generate output table: 2029E Revenue, EBITDA, EBITDA Margin, Net Income, EPS, FCF, FCF Margin
3. Calculate Cumulative FCF 2025-2029 for each scenario
4. Document rationale for each scenario""" ;
    oc:stepOrder 8 .

oc:kn_cee00a81 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When extracting financials from SEC filings (Step 1)" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Historical financial extraction from 10-K:
1. Download latest 10-K from SEC EDGAR (Item 8)
2. Create [Company]_Historical_Financials_[Date].xlsx
3. Extract Income Statement (3-5 years): Revenue, COGS, Gross Profit, OpEx by type, EBITDA, EBIT, Interest, Tax, Net Income, EPS, Shares
4. Extract Cash Flow (3-5 years): CFO, D&A, SBC, WC changes, CapEx, Acquisitions, Debt, Equity, Dividends
5. Extract Balance Sheet (3-5 years): Current/Non-current Assets & Liabilities, Equity
6. Calculate Historical Metrics: Revenue growth, margins (gross/EBITDA/op/net/FCF), ROIC, D/E, Current ratio
7. Document sources in Notes sheet""" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_ea07a5ea a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building the Scenarios tab in Step 8" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Build three scenarios (Bull/Base/Bear) with clearly differentiated assumptions for revenue CAGR, margins, and CapEx. Document the rationale for each scenario." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Scenario analysis shows the range of outcomes and demonstrates analytical rigor to institutional investors" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_f722fdd6 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before beginning any modeling work" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before starting, verify access to 10-K/10-Q filings for public companies or financial statements for private companies. If unavailable, stop and obtain them. Optionally check if Task 1 (company research) is complete for business context." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without reliable source financial data, the model will be built on guesses rather than audited figures" .

oc:kn_fe9054b2 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:directiveContent """Excel file with 6 tabs:
1. Revenue Model (product 20-30 rows, geography 15-20 rows, channel)
2. Income Statement (40-50 line items, historical + 5yr projections)
3. Cash Flow Statement (operating/investing/financing, FCF)
4. Balance Sheet (35-45 line items, balance check row)
5. Scenarios (Bull/Base/Bear assumptions + outputs)
6. DCF Inputs (NOPAT, Unlevered FCF, terminal year metrics)
File: [Company]_Financial_Model_[Date].xlsx""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Company",
        "Date" .

